- `src/ui/offlineModal.js` (new): `calcOfflineProgress(saveTs, rates, resources, caps)` — calculates `elapsed = min(realElapsed, 28800s / 8h)`; if elapsed ≥ 30s, applies `rate × elapsed` delta to each resource (capped at `caps[id]`, floored at 0), mutates `resources` in-place, returns `{ elapsed, gains }` or `null`. `showOfflineModal(elapsed, gains)` — creates `#offline-modal` `.modal-overlay`; renders welcome-back header with moon icon and formatted time string (`Xh Ym` or `Xm`), per-resource gain/loss rows (filtered to |delta| ≥ 1, green for gains, red for losses); gold "Continue →" button (`.btn--ng-start`); dismisses on button click, Enter, Escape, or click-outside; cleans up keydown listener on close.
- `src/main.js`: added `_pendingOffline` module var; `_applySave()` calls `calcOfflineProgress(save.ts, state.rates, state.resources, state.caps)` after `recalcRates()` and stores result in `_pendingOffline`; `boot()` calls `showOfflineModal(_pendingOffline.elapsed, _pendingOffline.gains)` after all UI panels are initialised, then clears `_pendingOffline`.
