- `game/src/main.js` — Imported `initChallenges` + `challengeTick`; registered `challengeTick` as 13th tick system; `initChallenges()` called in boot + `_newGame()`; `_newGame()` applies `opts.archetype` to `state.archetype`; wizard call updated to pass `state.archetype ?? 'none'`; `_save()` adds `challenges` + `archetype` fields (save version bumped to 19); `_applySave()` restores both with `?? null` / `?? 'none'` defaults for backward compatibility.

- `game/.intel/tasks.json` — T061 + T062 added and marked done with full implementation notes.

- `game/styles/main.css` — T061 styles: `.challenge-section` (bg-card, border, radius, padding), `.challenge-header`, `.challenge-card/--active/--waiting` (blue-tinted active card, dashed waiting card), `.challenge-card__top/.icon/.label/.timer/--urgent` (red glow when <30s), `.challenge-card__desc/.reward`, `.challenge-progress` with `.progress-bar__fill--challenge` (blue gradient), `.challenge-completed/__header/__entry/__reward`. T062 styles: `.arch-buttons` flex row, `.btn--arch/.btn--arch-active` (gold border+tint on active), `.ng-arch-desc/.ng-arch-bonuses/.ng-arch-bonus-line` (green bonus lines), `.summary-empire-badge--arch` (gold pill, faint gold bg). Mobile: arch buttons column, challenge timer wraps.

**Architecture decisions:**
- Challenge templates use `target(cur)` to compute an absolute threshold at generation time, stored in `active.target`. Completion check is simply `metric() >= active.target`, which is uniform across all types and survives save/load without re-computation.
- The `startValue` stored in `active` lets the progress bar show meaningful % even when the metric is an absolute value (e.g. total territory, total wins). `(cur - startValue) / (target - startValue)` correctly shows how much of the challenge is done since it began.
- The `CHALLENGE_UPDATED` event is the single source of truth for quest panel re-renders; the TICK handler provides per-second countdown updates only when an active challenge exists — minimising unnecessary renders.
- Archetype bonuses are applied at compute time (recalcRates, castSpell, attackTile, scaledCost) rather than stored as modified rates, so changing archetype on a new game is immediately correct without needing to invalidate cached values.
- `state.archetype` is intentionally NOT reset in `initState()` — it persists like `difficulty` so players who prefer a playstyle keep it across New Game restarts without needing to re-select.
- The Arcane mana cost reduction in `spells.js` uses the effective `manaCost` variable (not `def.manaCost`) for both the affordability check and the deduction, so the reduction is always consistent.
- Conqueror building cost reduction applies inside `scaledCost()` which is shared by all building construction paths (normal build, wonder build) ensuring the discount is universal.
- Save version bumped from 17 → 19 (18 reserved for challenges, 19 for archetype); both fields use `?? null` / `?? 'none'` defaults in `_applySave()` so saves from v17 and earlier load cleanly.

