### T066 — Tile Fortification

**Summary:** Players can spend 40 stone + 25 iron to fortify any player-owned tile (except the capital). Fortified tiles gain +15 defense, making them significantly harder for enemies to retake. The improvement picker modal is extended with a Fortify button/badge. Fortified tiles show a blue `▲` indicator on the canvas. Enemy capture removes the fortification.

**Files changed:**

- `game/src/core/actions.js` — Added `fortifyTile(x, y)`: validates tile ownership, non-capital, not-already-fortified, resource cost (40 stone + 25 iron); sets `tile.fortified = true`, `tile.defense += 15`; emits MAP_CHANGED + RESOURCE_CHANGED; shows build log message.

- `game/src/ui/mapPanel.js` — Imported `fortifyTile`. In `_createImprovementPicker()`, added `data-fortify` click handler. In `_showImprovementPicker()`: computed `fortifySection` (shows "🏰 Fortified (+15 defense)" badge if already fortified, or Fortify button with cost and disabled state if resources insufficient); inserted fortifySection into all 3 modal states (already-improved, no-improvement, can-build); renamed modal header to "Tile Actions". In `_drawTile()`: draws small blue `▲` glyph in tile top-right for `tile.fortified && tile.owner === 'player'` (non-capital). In `_showTileTip()`: shows 🏰 emoji next to defense value for fortified tiles; adds a dim hint line "Click → Fortify (+15 def)" for unfortified player tiles.

- `game/src/systems/enemyAI.js` — On enemy tile capture, clears `tile.fortified = false` and subtracts 15 from `tile.defense`. Fortified tiles get -30% enemy counterattack win chance (`winChance *= 0.70`).

- `game/styles/main.css` — Added `.imp-fortify-row` (flex between label and button), `.imp-fortify-label`, `.btn--fortify` (blue border/text, disabled state), `.imp-fortified` (blue tinted confirmation badge).

**Architecture decisions:**
- Policy effects are applied to **positive rates only** in `recalcRates()` to avoid accidentally reducing unit upkeep consumption (which would be a net positive). The per-resource `effects` map and the `allRatesMult` global multiplier both apply only when `rate[res] > 0`.
- The 60-second cooldown is only enforced when switching **away from** an active policy (not when removing it entirely), so deactivating doesn't trigger cooldown.
- Tile fortification uses a separate `tile.fortified` boolean rather than overloading the `tile.improvement` field, so players can have both a terrain improvement (e.g. Farm) AND a fortification on the same tile.
- Save version bumped from 20 → 21 to include `policy` and `policyChangedAt` in persisted state. Old saves load cleanly with `?? null` / `?? -999` defaults.

