**T068: Garrison System**

**Files modified:**
- `game/src/core/state.js` — Added `garrisons: null` field; reset in `initState()`.
- `game/src/core/events.js` — Added `GARRISON_CHANGED: 'garrisonChanged'` event constant.
- `game/src/core/actions.js` — `garrisonUnit(x,y,unitId,count)`: validates ownership/non-capital/army count/food cost (30/unit)/total cap (10 across all tiles); removes from `state.units`, stores in `state.garrisons['x,y']`. `withdrawGarrison(x,y)`: returns units to army, frees slot. `destroyGarrison(x,y)`: silently removes garrison on enemy capture (no refund, combat-loss message). Exported `getTotalGarrisoned()` and `GARRISON_MAX_TOTAL`.
- `game/src/systems/resources.js` — Garrison upkeep loop in `recalcRates()` iterates `state.garrisons` values and applies `UNITS[unitId].upkeep` per garrisoned unit.
- `game/src/systems/enemyAI.js` — Imported `destroyGarrison`. Adds garrison unit defense values to `playerDefense` for the specific attacked tile before computing `winChance`. Calls `destroyGarrison(x,y)` when enemy captures tile.
- `game/src/ui/mapPanel.js` — Imported `UNITS`, `garrisonUnit`, `withdrawGarrison`, `getTotalGarrisoned`, `GARRISON_MAX_TOTAL`. `GARRISON_CHANGED` listener triggers re-render. `_drawTile` draws yellow 🛡count in bottom-left corner. Tile tooltip shows garrison unit type + count + defense bonus. `_garrisonSection(x,y,tile)` builds picker HTML (existing garrison: unit badge + Withdraw; no garrison: per-unit-type buttons with food cost). All 3 picker states include garrison section. `_createImprovementPicker` handles `data-garrison` (station) and `data-withdraw-garrison` (withdraw) clicks.
- `game/src/main.js` — `garrisons` added to `_save()` payload and `_applySave()` restore (`?? null`). Save version bumped 21 → 22.
- `game/styles/main.css` — `.imp-garrison` gold-tinted container, `.imp-garrison__header/current/limit/units`, `.btn--garrison-unit` (gold hover), `.btn--garrison-withdraw` (red hover).

**Architecture decisions:**
- Ceasefire tick stored on each empire object (inside `state.diplomacy.empires[]`) — automatically included in the existing `state.diplomacy` save payload without needing a separate top-level field.
- `payTribute` and `demandTribute` share the same `ceasefireTick` mechanism — paying tribute buys peace, demanding tribute also triggers ceasefire (the faction is paying you, so they're not raiding). The distinction is directionality and gold gain/loss.
- Garrison units are removed from `state.units` (reducing attack power and army display) to make the positioning choice meaningful — you trade mobile army strength for static defense.
- Garrison upkeep is calculated separately in `recalcRates()` (since garrisoned units are removed from `state.units`) to maintain economic balance.
- `GARRISON_MAX_TOTAL=10` prevents late-game abuse of garrisoning every tile; the 30 food/unit cost provides an upfront penalty discouraging casual overuse.
- `destroyGarrison()` is exported from `actions.js` (not `enemyAI.js`) to keep all state mutations in one module.

**Next session should tackle:**
- T069+: More Phase 7 features — consider enemy faction tribute demands (AI demands tribute from player), unit merging/stacking improvements, or map territory analytics panel.

