**Architecture decisions:**
- Landmarks are placed in `initMap()` so they exist from the very start of every new game — creating consistent strategic targets regardless of RNG timing.
- The `tile.landmark` property persists in `state.map.tiles` (already saved as part of `state.map`), so no extra serialization is needed beyond the `state.landmarks.captured` tracker.
- Building specializations are stored as `state.buildingSpecials = { [buildingId]: specId }` — one slot per building type (not per building count). This means specializing a Farm affects all your Farm buildings, which is intentional and makes the choice more impactful.
- The barracks `training_grounds` trainTimeMult (0.75) is applied directly in `trainUnit()` (like warcraft tech) rather than in `_advanceTrainingQueue()`, so the `totalTicks` stored in the queue entry correctly reflects the specialization at the time of training.
- Armory combatMult is applied alongside (and after) council boon mult and before War Banner, matching the layering order of other multipliers.

