- `game/src/ui/militaryPanel.js`: Imported `canEnshrineHero/enshrineHero/ENSHRINE_MAX` from heroSystem; subscribed `HERO_ENSHRINED→_render`; added `_heroEnshrineSection()` — amber-bordered panel showing progress toward enshrine requirements, status line (needs X skills / X victories / ready / maxed), and Enshrine button when `canEnshrineHero()`; added `skillsNeeds(n)` helper; added `_heroLegacyPanel()` — gold-bordered panel showing enshrined champion cards with rate pill badges; updated `_heroSection()` to show legacy count in subtitle + `_heroLegacyPanel()` below recruit button; updated active hero section to include `_heroEnshrineSection()` after legendary quest section; added `enshrine-hero` data-action click handler.
- `game/src/main.js`: Imported `ENSHRINE_PRESTIGE` from heroSystem; `HERO_ENSHRINED` listener awards 200 prestige; `heroLegacy` included in save payload + `_applySave()`.
- `game/styles/main.css`: `.enshrine-section` (amber left-border, subtle bg), `.enshrine-section__header/desc`, `.enshrine-status/--ready/--maxed`, `.btn--enshrine` (amber gradient), `.hero-legacy-panel`, `.legacy-hero-card`, `.legacy-rate` pill badges.

**Architecture decisions:**
- Crisis penalties are pushed directly to `state.randomEvents.activeModifiers` (same format as disaster modifiers) so they integrate seamlessly with the existing `recalcRates()` penalty system, including the Grand Cathedral wonder's halving of disaster severity.
- Crisis spawning is blocked until at least one game-tick cycle after boot/load (nextCrisisTick is set ahead by _nextInterval() in initCrises), so players aren't immediately hit with a crisis at game start.
- The crisis banner uses DOM-based innerHTML re-render (not a full panel system) since it's a transient overlay — the delegated click listener on the parent div survives innerHTML updates.
- Hero legacy bonuses are computed once at enshrinement time and stored as a simple `{res→val}` rates object — avoids re-evaluating skill chains on every tick and makes saved data human-readable.
- LEGACY_RATES_BY_SKILL converts ALL 10 skills to resource rate bonuses (not just the 4 that already give rates), so no skill choice leaves a hero with zero legacy value. Combat-oriented skills convert to gold income (tribute/glory), training/research skills to iron/mana.
- Maximum 2 enshrinements per game prevents infinite stacking; ENSHRINE_MAX is an exported constant so UI and logic use the same value.

