**Architecture decisions:**
- Wonders intentionally gate on Medieval Age (age===3) without a save-version migration because state.wonder=null on new games and the field is always initialized by initWonders() on boot — older saves without the field safely get null via the ?? null fallback in _applySave.
- The Grand Colosseum +10 morale applies once on completion via changeMorale() rather than being recalculated each tick — this is correct because morale is a semi-persistent value with its own drift, not a rate.
- Grand Bazaar trade multiplier is applied in the buy/sell functions themselves (not as a rate bonus) so it compounds naturally with market price fluctuations and seasonal premium pricing.
- Tower of Babel research time reduction stacks multiplicatively with all other modifiers (arcane_tome, war_scholar, workshop discount, etc.) — order-independent since all are multiplied together.
- Scholar activeEffect is a single slot (not an array) because only one teaching can be active at a time — accepting a new teaching while one is running would replace it, but the system prevents this since visits only spawn when no visit is active.
- Engineering Plans discount is applied in scaledCost() (shared by all build paths) rather than in buildBuilding() directly, ensuring it also works with any future build paths that call scaledCost.
- Scholar visits only spawn when state.scholar.active === null, preventing overlap with expiry mechanics.

