**Architecture decisions:**
- Records are stored in their own separate localStorage key (`'empireos-records'`) to survive both manual save deletion and new-game resets.
- `updateRecords()` is called both on GAME_OVER (natural win/loss) and in `_newGame()` (player starts new game without the game over screen) to ensure no session is missed.
- No save version bump needed: records live in a separate localStorage key and have no migration concern.
